            <p:rationale>The identity management environment ensures that authorizations are defined and enforced in an efficient, reliable, traceable and controllable manner. The identity management environment ensures that all access to IT systems is authenticated, that authentications are uniformly implemented and that only once users having to log on.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>An identity management environment will be furnished, affording a central administration of identities, roles and authorizations. There is also a provisioning environment; users, roles and authorizations will propagate from authoritative sources to target systems. There are authentication and authorization services that enforce secure access to IT systems. Imports of identities in the authoritative source are monitored and carefully placed in accordance with previously established procedures and guidelines. There are no users manually implemented in target systems and directories. Users have only one account and password which they can gain access to all systems without having to login again. </p:implications>
